                                      <tr>
                                        <td colspan="2"><div align="center" class="style45">Westmuir Defibrillator Project Receives Funding Boost </div></td>
                                      </tr>
                                      <tr>
                                        <td colspan="2"><div align="center">
                                          <p>At the Westmuir Community Development Trust AGM on Tuesday 5th February,  it was announced that a generous bequest of <strong>&pound;1,500</strong> has been donated to the <strong>Westmuir Defibrillator Project</strong> in memory of <strong>Mr Jim Walkden</strong>.<br />
                                            This wonderful gift will ensure the success of the project and was given by his wife <strong>Mary </strong>and their<strong> son James </strong>and<strong> daughter Clare</strong>. </p>
                                          <p>As a result, the local project team is now able to move ahead and will keep the community and Mrs Walkden and her family fully informed of its progress. All those present at the Trust Annual Meeting expressed there sincere thanks to Mrs Walkden and family for their wonderful generosity.</p>
                                        </div></td>
                                      </tr>
                                      <tr>
                                        <td colspan="2"><div align="center">
                                          <hr />
                                        </div></td>
                                      </tr>
                                      <tr>
                                        <td colspan="2"><div align="center" class="style45">Westmuir Community Development Trust AGM Held </div></td>
                                      </tr>
                                      <tr>
                                        <td colspan="2"><p align="center">The <strong>14th Annual General Meeting</strong> of the <strong>Westmuir Community Development Trust</strong> was held in the village hall on <strong>5th February 2019</strong> where those present received the Directors' Annual report and the Annual Accounts for the year ending 31st October 2018. </p>
                                          <p align="center">The Annual Report and Accounts as well as the Minutes of the AGM are available by clicking on the following links:</p>
                                          <p align="center"><a href="PDF Pages/Annual Report and Accounts 2017-2018 (2).pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Trustees' Annual Report incorporating the Report of the Directors.</strong></a></p>
                                          <p align="center"><a href="PDF Pages/Minute of 14th AGM (1).pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Minutes of the AGM held on 5th Feb 2019 </strong></a></p></td>
                                      </tr>
